properties.FacilityDescription:
Overview

Bolding Mill Campground is an excellent choice for camping on Lake Sidney Lanier, offering plenty of comfortable amenities in addition to a well-kept facility.

Visitors will enjoy fishing and boating on the lake as well as the lush picnic area and large swimming beach, perfect for families.

Natural Features:

Lake Lanier spans 38,000 acres and five counties in northern Georgia. The reservoir is known for its aqua-blue coloring and spectacular scenery in the forested foothills of the Blue Ridge Mountains.

Bolding Mill campground is on the northwest side of the lake, which has plenty of grass and shade for comfortable camping.

Recreation:

The large swimming beach is a very popular spot to lay out and cool off during summer months.

An on-site boat ramp provides easy access to the lake for campers looking to spend a day on the water.

Bolding Mill is also connected to hiking trails for plenty of opportunities to enjoy the scenery and bird watch.

Facilities:

The campground offers 88 sites with electric and water hookups. Theres also nine tent-only sites. Campground conveniences include a laundry facility, playground, hot showers and a swimming beach.

Nearby Attractions:

Head to the Don Carter State Park for birding and hiking opportunities. Another idea is the Sawnee Mountain Preserve, with breathtaking scenic overlooks, hiking opportunities and rock climbing.
properties.FacilityDirections: From Atlanta, GA, take SR 400 north to Exit 17, turn right on GA Hwy306, turn right on GA Hwy 53, turn left on Old Sardis Rd, and turn lefton Chestatee Rd.  Follow into campground.
